cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DB

This paper is about improving the accuracy of a machine learning model while preserving differential privacy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses sensitivity and privacy budget, which are key aspects of differential privacy, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of decision trees and boosting algorithms suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses experiments and results, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.DB (Databases).
